1. OWNERSHIP

The L7 system — including its 7-dimensional Common Lingua, Gateway architecture,
Universal OS translations, tool schemas, flow engine, MCP server implementations,
web interfaces, adapters, registry, correspondence tables, and all constituent
source code, documentation, and design — is the exclusive intellectual property
of Alberto Valido Delgado ("The Founder"), sole architect and originator.


2. NON-COMMERCIAL USE

Free. Always. Universal access.

Any individual, researcher, educator, student, or organization may use, copy,
modify, and distribute the L7 system for any non-commercial purpose, free of
charge, provided that this license notice and attribution to the Founder are
included in all copies or substantial portions of the software.

No fee. No registration. No approval required.


3. COMMERCIAL USE

Any entity that derives commercial revenue from the L7 system, any of its
components, or any application built upon the L7 architecture or Universal
OS shall pay a licensing fee to the Founder.

   a. FEE: 12% (twelve percent) of gross commercial revenue derived from
      the licensed technology.

      This rate is uniform. No caps. No tiers. No sliding scale.
      One rate for all commercial licensees, regardless of size.

      "Gross commercial revenue" means all revenue directly attributable
      to products, services, or operations that incorporate, depend on,
      or are built upon L7 tools, architecture, or derivatives thereof.

   b. ONGOING: The fee applies for the duration of commercial use. It is
      a revenue share, not a one-time payment. Licensees report and remit
      quarterly, or on a schedule agreed in the licensing agreement.

   c. PROCESS: Contact AVLI Cloud LLC to establish a written licensing
      agreement. Good-faith negotiation. Written agreement executed.
      Reporting and payment commence. Licensing relationship established.

   d. DERIVATIVE WORKS: Any software, service, product, or system that
      incorporates, extends, or is substantially based on L7 architecture,
      schemas, or code is a derivative work and subject to this license.
      This includes applications built on the L7 Universal OS.

   e. PRIOR COMMERCIAL TERMS: Licensees who entered into commercial
      agreements under prior versions of this license (see Section 13)
      are governed by the terms in effect at the time of their agreement.
      This section applies to new commercial relationships entered on or
      after March 6, 2026.


4. LICENSEE RIGHTS

Upon execution of a commercial licensing agreement:

   a. License to use all L7 tools commercially for the duration of the
      agreement.
   b. Freedom to use, modify, and deploy as the licensee sees fit,
      subject to reporting obligations.
   c. No per-seat charges. No minimum fees. Revenue share only.
   d. If a licensee generates zero revenue in a reporting period,
      zero is owed. The fee is proportional to success.


5. THE FOUNDER'S ROLE

The Founder creates tools. The Founder collects the licensing fee for
commercial use. The Founder does not monitor, enforce, judge, or restrict
how the tools are used beyond the reporting obligations in the licensing
agreement.

How the tools are used is the licensee's decision and responsibility. Existing
laws in all applicable jurisdictions govern the conduct of all parties.


6. FOUNDER'S RIGHT

The Founder retains perpetual, irrevocable, unrestricted, and free access to
every tool, component, and derivative work created by, through, or under the
L7 system. This right cannot be overridden, sublicensed away, or extinguished
by any contract, agreement, acquisition, merger, or transfer of ownership.


7. RESTRICTIONS

   a. No entity may claim ownership of L7 or its derivatives without written
      consent from the Founder.
   b. No entity may sublicense L7 rights to third parties without written
      consent from the Founder.
   c. No entity may remove, alter, or obscure this license or the Founder's
      attribution from any distribution.
   d. The L7 name and terminology are the exclusive property of the Founder.


8. SUCCESSION AND CONTINUITY

This license and all rights, obligations, and terms herein shall survive the
death, incapacity, or unavailability of the Founder. Upon such event:

   a. All intellectual property rights transfer to the successor entity
      designated in the AVLI Cloud LLC Operating Agreement and/or the
      Founder's revocable living trust.
   b. The licensing terms remain unchanged. The revenue share structure,
      the non-commercial freedom, and existing licensing agreements
      continue in full force.
   c. The proof of authorship (git history, salt seals, original artifacts)
      exists independently and speaks for itself regardless of the
      Founder's availability.
   d. No party may use the Founder's death, incapacity, or unavailability
      as grounds to claim the IP is abandoned, orphaned, or in the public
      domain. The copyright endures for the Founder's life plus 70 years
      per 17 USC § 302.
   e. Successor trustees or members shall continue licensing operations
      under these same terms, guided by the principle that all purpose of
      this work is to serve the greatest good of humanity.


9. LAWFUL USE

This license is granted to parties operating within the law. The Founder
does not monitor, investigate, or enforce how tools are used. However:

   a. If a licensee's use of L7 tools is found by a court of competent
      jurisdiction to be connected with criminal activity, the license
      granted herein is not a defense to criminal liability. The license
      governs commercial use of software; it does not authorize, condone,
      or protect unlawful conduct.
   b. The Founder's licensing fee (Section 3) applies equally to all
      commercial users regardless of the nature of their business.
      The fee is for the use of the tools, not an endorsement of the
      user's conduct.
   c. Criminal matters are governed by the applicable criminal law of
      the relevant jurisdiction. The Founder has no role in criminal
      enforcement and makes no representations about any user's conduct.


