13. LICENSE HISTORY AND PRIOR VERSIONS

The L7 system has been distributed under three license schedules. Each
schedule applied to the versions distributed during its period. Recipients
of prior versions retain the rights granted under the terms that accompanied
those versions. No schedule is retroactive.

   a. MIT RESEARCH PERIOD (January 12, 2026 — February 27, 2026)

      The earliest versions of L7 were distributed with an MIT license
      reference in package.json metadata. No formal MIT LICENSE text file
      was included in the repository. During this period:

      - The repository had 0 forks, 0 watchers, and 0 external contributors
      - The package was never published to npm or any registry
      - No third party is known to have received or used these versions

      Any party that did receive the L7 source code during this period
      retains MIT rights to the specific version they received. Those
      rights do not extend to versions released after February 27, 2026.

   b. FIRST PROPRIETARY PERIOD (February 27, 2026 — March 5, 2026)

      The license was changed to a proprietary license with the following
      commercial terms: 10% of profit attributable to L7 components,
      calculated proportionally to L7 usage, paid as a one-time fee.

      Any party that entered into a commercial licensing agreement during
      this period is governed by those terms. No such agreements exist
      as of the date of this revision.

   c. CURRENT SCHEDULE (March 6, 2026 — present)

      The license was revised to the current terms: 12% of gross
      commercial revenue derived from the licensed technology, paid as
      an ongoing revenue share. One rate, no caps, no tiers, no sliding
      scale. This schedule governs all new commercial relationships.

This license, as revised, governs the current version and all future
versions of the L7 system.


